    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This powerplant utilizes individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver linear power up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Shifting is handled by a precise Getrag 6-speed manual transmission paired with a factory limited-slip differential. The chassis exhibits excellent torsional rigidity, with a recently inspected subframe and refreshed bushings ensuring sharp turn-in via the MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension. While showing minor cosmetic patina consistent with a well-loved performance vehicle, it remains mechanically robust with a documented service history. This M3 offers a pure, analog connection to the road that modern sports cars struggle to replicate.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
